gomodel:SYNGO_2059  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099060 replaced by GO:0099634" , "Rationale: \"To reveal the α3 subunit, we carried out both immunoperoxidase and silver-intensified immunogold reactions. As the α3 antibody recognized an extracellular epitope, the peroxidase reaction end product was observed primarily associated with the plasma membrane of the postsynaptic specialization of symmetric synapses (Figure (Figure4A).4A). However, due to its diffusion, the presynaptic active zone and some intracellular organelles located immediately underneath the postsynaptic membrane appeared also labeled (Figure (Figure4A).4A). On the other hand, silver-gold particles were directly observed at the postsynaptic membrane within the main body of symmetric synapses thus demonstrating a restricted localization of the α3 subunit to postsynaptic elements (Figure (Figure4B).4B)\"\n\nNote: staining is more centered around the postsynapse. No quantification was included.\n\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: \"Functional expression of the GABAA receptor α2 and α3 subunits at synapses between intercalated medial paracapsular neurons of mouse amygdala\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2059" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

